---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Customer Reviews and Local SEO Guide | visibilite-locale.online"
  description="How to get, manage and respond to Google reviews to improve your local SEO and online reputation."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
      <nav class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <a href="/en/" class="hover:text-blue-600">Home</a> &rsaquo;
        <a href="/en/guide-seo-local" class="hover:text-blue-600">Local SEO Guide</a> &rsaquo;
        <span class="text-gray-900">Customer Reviews</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">Customer Reviews and Local SEO</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        How to get and manage your Google reviews to improve your visibility and local reputation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 prose">
      <h2>The impact of reviews on local SEO</h2>
      <p>
        Google reviews are one of the main ranking factors in the local pack. The number of reviews, average rating, and frequency of new reviews directly influence your positioning.
      </p>

      <h2>Getting more authentic reviews</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Ask for a review after each successful service, when the customer is most satisfied</li>
        <li>Simplify the process with a direct link to your Google listing</li>
        <li>Add a QR code on your physical materials (business card, receipt, storefront)</li>
        <li>Send a follow-up email or SMS with your listing link</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Responding to reviews</h2>
      <p>
        Responding to all reviews, both positive and negative, shows you care about your customers. Google values businesses that actively engage with their reviews.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Positive reviews</strong>: thank the customer by name and mention the service or product</li>
        <li><strong>Negative reviews</strong>: stay professional, acknowledge the issue, and offer a solution</li>
        <li><strong>Fake reviews</strong>: report them to Google through your GBP listing</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Keywords in reviews</h2>
      <p>
        Keywords used by customers in their reviews help Google understand your business. Naturally encourage customers to mention the service or product in their comment.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Related articles</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 text-blue-700">
          <li><a href="/en/blog/en-avis-clients-seo/">Customer Reviews and Local SEO</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
